<p><num value="45">45</num>. <hi rend=italics>Rembrandt</hi>. The Woman taken in Adultery-<num value="1">one</num> of the finest of Rembrandt's cabinet pictures. The sorrow and repentance of the woman are vividly expressed, though she is a great lady repenting in a train. Painted for Jan <num value="6">Six</num>, Heer van Vromade, in <datestruct value="1644--"><year reg="1644">1644</year></datestruct>. 
