<p><num value="66">66</num>. <hi rend=italics>Rubens</hi>. The Chateau of Stein, near Malines--from the Palazzo Balbi, at Genoa--the residence of the painter in the rich wooded scenery of Brabant. 
   <p><QUOTE rend=blockquote><CIT><QUOTE>Seldom as he practised it, Rubens was never greater than in landscape. The tumble of his rocks and trees, the deep shadows in his shades and glooms, the watery sunshine and the dewy verdure, show a variety of genius which are not to be found in the inimitable but uniform productions of Claude.</QUOTE><BIBL>-Horace Walpole.</BIBL></CIT></QUOTE>
 
<p><num value="194">194</num>. <hi rend=italics>Rubens</hi>. The Judgment of Paris--a picture greatly studied by artists. In allusion to the evils which resulted from the Judgment, the figure of Discord appears in the air. <pb id="p.24" n="24"> 
