<p>*<num value="33">33</num>. <hi rend=italics>Parmigiano</hi>. The Vision of St. Jerome-painted, by order of Maria Bufalina, in <datestruct value="1527--"><year reg="1527">1527</year></datestruct>, for the Church of San Salvatore in Lauro at Citta di Castello. Though the artist was only in his <num value="24">twenty-fourth</num> year when he executed it, this is a most noble picture. It is supposed to be that which so absorbed the painter's attention during the siege of Rome by the Constable de Bourbon, that he was unaware the city was taken till some German soldiers, bursting in to plunder his house, were overwhelmed with its beauty, and not only spared, but protected him. 
