<p>*<hi rend=italics>Sir J. Reynolds</hi>. The glorious Portrait of Mrs. Siddons as the Tlagic Muse, painted in <datestruct value="1785--"><year reg="1785">1785</year></datestruct>. The want of colour in the face is owing <pb id="p.93" n="93"> to the great actress's own request at her last sitting that Sir Joshua would <QUOTE>not heighten that tone of complexion so accordant with the chilly and concentrated musings of pale melancholy.</QUOTE> Remorse and Pity appear like ghosts in the background. Reynolds inscribed his name on the border of the drapery, telling Mrs. Siddons that he could not resist the opportunity of going down to posterity on the hem of her garment. 
